Bauchi State Commissioner for Commerce and Industry Al-Hassan Sadiq has resigned from Governor Bala Mohammed’s cabinet. Sadiq, who posted his resignation on his Facebook page on Wednesday night said “Alhamdulillah, Masha Allah. Every beginning has an end. Today August 19 2020, I have honourably tendered my resignation as a Commissioner (Ministry of Commerce & Industries) and a Member of the State Executive Council in the government of Bauchi State. It was a rare privilege and opportunity to have served my state in such an exalted position.” “I thank H.E the Executive Governor – Sen Bala A. Mohammed (Kauran Bauchi) for the wonderful opportunity accorded me. In the same vein, I must appreciate my boss, H.E, the Rt. Hon. Yakubu Dogara for his usual support and the role he played in influencing same. “I sincerely thank all my colleagues in the EXCO and the Ministry, who I worked with. I have enjoyed the understanding of my family at such a trying time. “I beseech God to forgive all my wrongs and the general public/colleagues to pardon me. I urge you to help me, pray God to grant me success, contentment and peace of mind in my new endeavour. Thank you all and remain blessed.” Sadiq’s resignation makes him the second commissioner to quit the cabinet after Nura Soro of finance ministry resigned barely three months in office.